item.dc:creator: @nuradonai nuradonai
item.description:
@nuradonai wrote:

Depends… What source are you using and what client? I’d try to just use your ip address and not no-ip first. To find your ip: Start---->Control Panel---->Network and Internet Connections---->Network Connections---->Right click on your connection and click status then click on the support tab and you see your ip try typing that in.
